%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69987b432237a6a8f0cd866e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225504%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20US%20Army%20held%20its%20first%20annual%20Best%20Drone%20Warfighter%20competition%20in%20Huntsville%2C%20Alabama%2C%20bringing%20operators%20from%20across%20the%20service%20to%20compete%20in%20two%20lanes.%3Cp%3EUS%20Army%20photo%20by%20Sgt.%20Aaron%20Troutman%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20Army%20is%20evaluating%20what%20types%20of%20criteria%2C%20like%20being%20a%20gamer%2C%20make%20the%20best%20drone%20pilots.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20service%20held%20its%20first%20annual%20Best%20Drone%20Warfighter%20competition%2C%20bringing%20together%20operators%20from%20across%20the%20service.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EArmy%20officials%20said%20the%20event%20helped%20them%20continue%20to%20evaluate%20training%20needs%20for%20drone%20pilots.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20Army%20used%20its%20first%20Best%20Drone%20Warfighter%20competition%20not%20just%20to%20test%20skills%2C%20officials%20say%2C%20but%20to%20identify%20what%20makes%20a%20top%20drone%20operator%20%E2%80%94%20and%20who%20in%20the%20force%20is%20best%20suited%20for%20the%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERather%20than%20training%20every%20soldier%20to%20fly%20drones%2C%20the%20Army%20is%20using%20competition%20to%20identify%20the%20skill%20sets%20of%20top%20drone%20operators%20and%20whether%20there%20are%20specific%20roles%20within%20units%20that%20would%20make%20the%20most%20sense%20for%20working%20with%20uncrewed%20aerial%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20effort%20reflects%20a%20broader%20shift%20from%20treating%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-army-learning-drone-lessons-bad-signals-broken-parts-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edrone%20flying%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20something%20for%20all%20soldiers%20to%20approaching%20it%20as%20a%20specialized%20skill%20set%20that%20requires%20the%20right%20aptitude%2C%20training%2C%20and%20sustained%20practice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20inaugural%20drone%20competition%20took%20place%20this%20week%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Alabama%20in%20Huntsville%2C%20gathering%20teams%20from%20across%20active%2C%20Reserve%2C%20and%20National%20Guard%20units.%20There%20were%20no%20requirements%20on%20what%20types%20of%20soldiers%20could%20participate%20or%20where%20they%20came%20from.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERather%2C%20%26quot%3Bit%20was%20just%20send%20your%20best%20UAS%20operators%2C%26quot%3B%20Col.%20Nicholas%20Ryan%2C%20director%20of%20Army%20UAS%20Transformation%20at%20the%20Aviation%20Center%20of%20Excellence%2C%20told%20reporters%2C%20prompting%20a%20mix%20of%20operators%20with%20different%20backgrounds%20and%20expertise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20three%20days%2C%20soldiers%20competed%20in%20multiple%20events%2C%20testing%20their%20piloting%20skills.%20The%20first%20was%20an%20obstacle%20course%20that%20operators%20navigated%20using%20first-person-view%20drones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%228192%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20soldier%20holds%20a%20drone%20controller.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69987c0b156648bc16a89591%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225464%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERecent%20US%20Department%20of%20Defense%20directives%20have%20prioritized%20the%20development%20and%20integration%20of%20drones%20across%20the%20Army.%3Cp%3EUS%20Army%20photo%20by%20Spc.%20Michelle%20Lessard-Terry%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20was%20a%20hunter-killer%20scenario%20in%20which%20teams%20used%20a%20reconnaissance%20drone%20to%20survey%20an%20array%20of%20targets%20and%20decide%20which%20were%20highest%20priority%20for%20simulated%20strikes%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-new-cheap-one-way-attack-drone-force-middle-east-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eone-way%20attack%20drones%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20competition%20didn't%20involve%20any%20kinetic%20strikes%3B%20instead%2C%20soldiers%20flew%20the%20drones%20into%20nets%20on%20the%20targets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20third%20event%20was%20focused%20on%20innovation.%20Soldiers%20could%20build%2C%20modify%2C%20and%20test%20their%20own%20drones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERyan%20said%20that%20the%20Army%20was%20taking%20notes%20throughout%20the%20competition%20on%20who%20the%20top%20operators%20were%2C%20calling%20it%20talent%20management.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAt%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bit's%20not%20about%20receiving%20trophies%20or%20awards%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20is%20about%20identifying%20what%20sets%20the%20top%20drone%20operators%20apart%20and%20figuring%20out%20how%20they%20developed%20those%20skills.%20The%20goal%2C%20he%20said%2C%20is%20to%20understand%20%26quot%3Bwhat%20lessons%20can%20we%20take%20from%20this%20to%20find%20out%20who%20the%20best%20operator%20is%20and%20how%20they%20became%20the%20best%20operator.%20What%20skills%20and%20resources%20and%20training%20allowed%20them%20to%20become%20the%20best%20operator%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESoldiers%20in%20the%20US%20and%20Ukraine%20have%20noticed%20that%20gamers%20make%20excellent%20drone%20pilots%2C%20as%20do%20soldiers%20who%20have%20experience%20piloting%20hobby%20drones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20something%20we're%20absolutely%20looking%20at%20right%20now%2C%26quot%3B%20Ryan%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EArmy%20leaders%20have%20previously%20noted%20a%20correlation%20between%20soldiers%20who%20grew%20up%20playing%20video%20games%20%E2%80%94%20or%20who%20are%20active%20gamers%20%E2%80%94%20and%20drone%20proficiency.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETroops%20who%20game%20have%20shown%20quick%20reflexes%2C%20precise%20hand-eye%20coordination%2C%20and%20strong%20spatial%20awareness%20that%20make%20them%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-army-captain-says-top-drone-pilots-are-video-gamers-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecompetent%20with%20drones%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20an%20exercise%20in%20Germany%20last%20fall%2C%20a%20US%20Army%20captain%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20the%20top%20pilots%20were%20soldiers%20who%20%26quot%3Bwhen%20they%20got%20off%20on%20Fridays%2C%20then%20go%20and%20play%20video%20games.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Army%20has%20been%20restructuring%20its%20approach%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpentagon-taps-companies-ukrainian-for-attack-drones-competition-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edrone%20warfare%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20rewriting%20its%20training%20and%20focusing%20on%20integrating%20soldiers%20with%20small%20drone%20training%20into%20front-line%20units.%20Lessons%20and%20approaches%20are%20being%20shared%20across%20the%20service%2C%20building%20a%20broader%20doctrine%20on%20how%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-army-mastering-drone-warfare-doesnt-mean-always-right-weapon-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EArmy%20is%20adopting%20drones%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%227720%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20quadcopter%20drone%20flies%20on%20a%20field%20with%20trees%20in%20the%20background.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69987c93efb52c8bd0de8bf2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225147%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20competition%20allowed%20Army%20leadership%20to%20learn%20more%20about%20the%20skillsets%20and%20backgrounds%20that%20make%20drone%20operators%20successful.%3Cp%3EUS%20Army%20photo%20by%20Sgt.%20Aaron%20Troutman%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ERyan%20said%20that%20the%20service%20is%20realizing%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnot-every-us-army-soldier-needs-a-drone-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eflying%20drones%3C%2Fa%3E%20needs%20to%20be%20a%20dedicated%20assignment.%20%26quot%3BYou%20can't%20be%20a%20squad%20rifleman%20and%20a%20drone%20operator%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20explaining%20that%20%26quot%3Bit's%20one%20or%20the%20other%20because%20you%20have%20to%20have%20the%20level%20of%20skill%20and%20expertise%20in%20operating%20and%20employing%20the%20drones.%20That's%20what%20you%20have%20to%20be%20good%20at%20and%20train%20at%20and%20focus%20on%20for%20most%20of%20your%20time.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20Army%20officials%20said%20efforts%20like%20the%20competition%20were%20demonstrating%20where%20drones%20best%20fit%20in%20a%20formation%20and%20what%20aspects%20of%20training%20are%20most%20important%20to%20maintain%20these%20highly%20perishable%20skills.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20most%20part%2C%20soldiers%20flew%20their%20drones%20successfully%2C%20but%20the%20Army%20did%20take%20note%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-army-drone-wins-hint-at-how-behind-it-is-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecommunication%20breakdowns%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20soldiers%20went%20through%20the%20hunter-killer%20lane%2C%20specifically%20getting%20drones%20into%20position%20and%20identifying%20and%20simulating%20strikes%20on%20targets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20an%20example%20of%20something%20we%20didn't%20anticipate%2C%20but%20it's%20absolutely%20standing%20out%20as%20that%20is%20something%20we%20as%20an%20Army%20need%20to%20do%20better%20on%2C%26quot%3B%20Ryan%20said.%20%26quot%3BIf%20we're%20going%20to%20proliferate%20these%20drones%20and%20want%20them%20to%20be%20more%20effective%20and%20lethal%2C%20we%20just%20need%20to%20improve%20on%20how%20our%20soldiers%20talk%20to%20each%20other%20to%20communicate%20when%20they're%20using%20them.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20future%20iterations%20of%20the%20Best%20Drone%20Warfighter%20competition%2C%20the%20Army%20hopes%20to%20include%20kinetic%20elements%20as%20well%20as%20electronic%20warfare%20and%20jamming%20to%20better%20replicate%20real-world%20scenarios.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnot-all-army-soldiers-can-fly-drones-scouting-talent-2026-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1771677901000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69987df4efb52c8bd0de8c2d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnot-all-army-soldiers-can-fly-drones-scouting-talent-2026-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Army's%20first%20annual%20Best%20Drone%20Warfighter%20competition%20shed%20some%20new%20light%20on%20the%20ideal%20backgrounds%20and%20skill%20sets%20for%20drone%20pilots.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22cpanella%40businessinsider.com%20(Chris%20Panella)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnot-all-army-soldiers-can-fly-drones-scouting-talent-2026-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22AI%20Will%20Enhance%20Efficiency%2C%20Not%20Replace%20Humans%2C%20Says%20Karan%20Adani%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22Artificial%20intelligence%20will%20not%20replace%20human%20beings%20entirely%20but%20will%20act%20as%20an%20efficiency%20enhancer%2C%20enabling%20fewer%20people%20to%20deliver%20higher%20output%2C%20Karan%20Adani%2C%20Managing%20Director%20of%20Adani%20Ports%20and%20SEZ%20Limited%2C%20said%20on%20Saturday.%22%2C%22published%22%3A1771677806000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-12%2F2c2fuqd8_karanadani_160x120_09_December_24.jpg%3Fim%3DFeatureCrop%2Calgorithm%3Ddnn%2Cwidth%3D1200%2Cheight%3D738%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fai-will-enhance-efficiency-not-replace-humans-says-karan-adani-11117889%23publisher%3Dnewsstand%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Artificial%20intelligence%20will%20not%20replace%20human%20beings%20entirely%20but%20will%20act%20as%20an%20efficiency%20enhancer%2C%20enabling%20fewer%20people%20to%20deliver%20higher%20output%2C%20Karan%20Adani%2C%20Managing%20Director%20of%20Adani%2