height%3D738%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2F88-nations-adopt-new-delhi-declaration-back-indias-ai-for-all-vision-11117837%23publisher%3Dnewsstand%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22India's%20vision%20for%20a%20democratised%20and%20inclusive%20artificial%20intelligence%20framework%20has%20received%20sweeping%20global%20endorsement%2C%20with%20the%20AI%20Impact%20Summit%202026%20concluding%20in%20the%20capital%20with%20the%20adoption%20of%20the%20New%20Delhi%20Declaration.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22More%20people%20want%20open%20relationships%2C%20but%20many%20don't%20last.%20A%20sex%20researcher%20shares%20the%203%20top%20reasons%20couples%20return%20to%20monogamy.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224992%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Couple%20holding%20hands%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6994982fd3c7faef0ece6280%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223744%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ENon-monogamy%20comes%20with%20its%20own%20challenges%2C%20Dr.%20Justin%20R.%20Garcia%2C%20the%20executive%20director%20of%20the%20Kinsey%20Institute%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3Cp%3EHinterhaus%20Productions%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EDr.%20Justin%20R.%20Garcia%2C%20head%20of%20the%20Kinsey%20Institute%2C%20said%20non-monogamy%20has%20gotten%20more%20popular.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHowever%2C%20he%20said%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopen-relationship-with-man-ten-years-older-2023-3%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eopen%20relationships%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20polyamory%20tend%20not%20to%20work%20for%20most%20people.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESome%20find%20non-monogamy%20to%20be%20too%20much%20work%20in%20practice.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EOpen%20relationships%20have%20gotten%20a%20cultural%20glow-up%20among%20younger%20adults.%20In%20practice%2C%20though%2C%20they're%20hard%20to%20pull%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20a%20lot%20of%20social%20media%20chatter%20where%20people%20in%20happy%20non-monogamous%20relationships%20report%20perks%20such%20as%20greater%20sexual%20satisfaction%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpolyamorous-wedding-commitment-ring-relationships-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emultiple%20deep%20partnerships%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20less%20restrictive%20love%20lives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20outside%20the%20tweets%2C%20threads%2C%20and%20curated%20Instagram%20grids%2C%20the%20story%20is%20a%20bit%20more%20nuanced.%20A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fsocial-trends%2F2023%2F09%2F14%2Fpublic-has-mixed-views-on-the-modern-american-family%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2023%20Pew%20Research%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%20Americans%20are%20divided%20on%20open%20marriages.%20Of%20about%205%2C000%20US%20adults%20surveyed%2C%2037%25%20found%20open%20marriages%20completely%20unacceptable.%20Younger%20generations%20approved%20more%20than%20anyone%20else%3A%20roughly%20half%20of%2018-%20to%2029-year-olds%20were%20accepting%20of%20open%20marriages.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDr.%20Justin%20R.%20Garcia%2C%20the%20executive%20director%20of%20the%20Kinsey%20Institute%2C%20has%20also%20witnessed%20the%20growing%20popularity%20of%20non-monogamy%20in%20his%20work.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20were%20talking%20about%20swinging%20in%20the%2060s%20and%2070s%2C%20but%20the%20language%20and%20the%20amount%20of%20attention%20to%20it%20changed%2C%20particularly%20over%20the%20last%20decade%2C%26quot%3B%20Garcia%20told%20Business%20Insider%2C%20citing%20Amy%20C.%20Moors%2C%20a%20sexuality%20scientist%20who%20noticed%20a%20steady%20increase%20in%20people%20searching%20for%20terms%20related%20to%20polyamory%20between%202006%20and%202015.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20showing%20interest%20and%20actually%20engaging%20in%20the%20activity%20are%20two%20different%20things.%20In%20his%20new%20book%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20Intimate%20Animal%2C%26quot%3B%20Garcia%20said%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2F27096488%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eresearch%20from%20his%20lab%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20the%20Kinsey%20Institute%2C%20one%20of%20the%20most%20prominent%20research%20centers%20for%20human%20sexuality%20and%20relationships%2C%20found%20that%20one%20in%20five%20single%20adults%20in%20the%20US%2C%20out%20of%20about%208%2C700%20studied%2C%20have%20had%20some%20kind%20of%20consensual%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmy-partner-is-monogamous-but-im-not-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enon-monogamous%20relationship%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20some%20point%20in%20their%20lives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226720%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Hands%20holding%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F699498c1e1ba468a96ac2a03%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224480%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EStudies%20suggest%20that%20more%20people%20have%20tried%20non-monogamy%20than%20maintained%20it%20long-term.%3Cp%3EVershinin%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20looking%20at%20the%20past%20five%20years%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.researchgate.net%2Fpublication%2F319232548_Estimates_and_Correlates_of_Engagement_in_Consensually_Non-Monogamous_Relationships%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eanother%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20Garcia's%2C%20however%2C%20that%20number%20dropped%20significantly%2C%20suggesting%20that%20%26quot%3Bmore%20people%20try%20it%20than%20decide%20that%20it%20is%20a%20lifelong%20relationship%20structure%20for%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20Garcia%20said.%20%26quot%3BIn%20my%20social%20networks%2C%20that's%20been%20my%20experience%20as%20well.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20doesn't%20mean%20that%20they%20never%20work%2C%20he%20added.%20According%20to%20multiple%20studies%2C%20%26quot%3Bwhile%20consensually%20open%20relationships%20might%20not%20work%20for%20everyone%2C%20or%20even%20for%20most%20people%2C%20there%20are%20many%20people%20for%20whom%20they%20do%20work%20perfectly%20well%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote%20in%20his%20book.%20Those%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpoly-vee-polyamorous-marriage-how-it-works-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehappy%20non-monogamous%20relationships%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20for%20example%2C%20don't%20fare%20psychologically%20or%20emotionally%20worse%20than%20content%20monogamous%20couples.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20terms%20of%20who's%20a%20good%20candidate%20for%20it%3F%20My%20cheeky%20answer%2C%20but%20it's%20actually%20true%2C%20is%20those%20people%20who%20really%20want%20to%20do%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Garcia%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20similar%20to%20'What's%20the%20right%20amount%20of%20sex%20that%20we%20should%20be%20having%3F'%20It's%20as%20much%20as%20you%20want.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20that%20doesn't%20mean%20open%20relationships%20work%20for%20everyone.%20Based%20on%20his%20research%2C%20Garcia%20shared%20the%20most%20common%20reasons%20non-monogamous%20partnerships%20don't%20work%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225465bf7a-886f-4264-a456-afba5e0c8929%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EIt%20takes%20work%20to%20balance%20partners%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224526%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Three%20people%20hugging%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69949a82e1ba468a96ac2a50%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223394%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDevoting%20enough%20time%20to%20your%20partners%20can%20be%20challenging.%3Cp%3EFG%20Trade%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjessica-fern-polysecure-book-consensual-nonmonogamy-polyamory-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emost%20common%20challenges%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20non-monogamous%20partnerships%20might%20be%20our%20own%20biology.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20such%20a%20fundamental%2C%20evolved%20drive%20to%20form%20intense%20pair%20bonds%2C%26quot%3B%20Garcia%20said%2C%20ones%20that%20biologists%20theorize%20helped%20us%20thrive%20as%20a%20species%20over%20time.%20In%20his%20book%2C%20he%20said%20that%20%26quot%3Bour%20brains%20don't%20appear%20particularly%20well-suited%20to%20processing%20intimacy%20with%20more%20than%20one%20partner%20at%20a%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20be%20it%20another%20romantic%20partner%20or%20a%20sexual%20fling.%20Even%20fantasies%20of%20threesomes%2C%20Garcia%20said%2C%20more%20often%20involve%20an%20existing%20partner.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20romance%20is%20most%20often%20defined%20by%20sustained%20attention%20and%20effort%2C%20then%20it%20becomes%20more%20difficult%20when%20one%20or%20both%20partners%20have%20other%20people%20to%20focus%20on.%20Introducing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopen-marriage-partner-moved-in-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ea%20new%20partner%3C%2Fa%3E%20into%20a%20shared%20home%20can%20cause%20friction%20with%20a%20spouse%2C%20as%20can%20skipping%20dinner%20with%20a%20spouse%20to%20spend%20it%20with%20another%20significant%20other.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGarcia%20said%20one%20of%20the%20%26quot%3Bprevailing%20rationales%26quot%3B%20for%20consensual%20non-monogamy%20is%20having%20%26quot%3Btoo%20much%20love%20to%20give.%26quot%3B%20However%2C%20he%20wrote%2C%20the%20opposite%20is%20true%3A%20%26quot%3BMost%20people%20don't%20have%20the%20biological%2C%20psychological%2C%20and%20social%20tools%20to%20love%20more%20than%20one%20person%20at%20a%20time.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228dc57517-1bd9-413e-9a76-65ab6179f71c%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EExtra%20communication%20can%20be%20a%20turn-off%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225336%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Couple%20holding%20hands%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69949af4d3c7faef0ece6309%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224002%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EHealthy%20non-monogamous%20relationships%20require%20extra%20communication%2C%20which%20some%20people%20are%20put%20off%20by.%3Cp%3ETom%20Werner%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20research%2C%20Garcia%20said%20the%20happiest%20non-monogamous%20couples%20have%20the%20same%20thing%20in%20common%3A%20%26quot%3BThey%20tend%20to%20engage%20in%20a%20lot%20of%20communication.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpolyamorous-couple-used-agile-scrum-to-improve-communication-jealousy-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E20-person%20polycule%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20uses%20a%20software%20engineer%20strategy%20called%20%26quot%3Bagile%20scrum%26quot%3B%20to%20resolve%20any%20relationship%20issues.%20It%20involves%20monthly%20reviews%2C%20discussion%20questions%2C%20and%20action%20points.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEven%20casual%20polyamorous%20encounters%20take%20substantial%20effort%20and%20negotiation%2C%26quot%3B%20Garcia%20wrote%2C%20including%20lots%20of%20communication.%20%26quot%3BWho%20needs%20more%20touch%3F%20Less%3F%20Who%20is%20feeling%20neglected%3F%20Who%20needs%20more%20time%20with%20whom%3F%20What%20is%20the%20state%20of%20things%20between%20each%20member%20of%20the%20polycule%20and%20each%20of%20the%20others%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20people%20find%20that%20level%20of%20frequent%2C%20in-depth%20communication%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopen-relationship-nonmonogamous-girlfriend-years-open-communication-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebuilds%20their%20intimacy%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20brings%20them%20closer.%20Still%2C%20for%20many%20people%2C%20it's%20just%20too%20much%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f7775cb2-789d-4bb8-b12c-870451eb3fae%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EIt%20can%20magnify%20issues%20instead%20of%20fixing%20them%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223840%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Couple%20hugging%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69949bade1ba468a96ac2a84%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222880%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ENon-monogamy%20can%20heighten%20existing%20issues%20like%20jealousy%20and%20mismatched%20libidos.%3Cp%3Egorodenkoff%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20any%20healthy%20relationship%2C%20Garcia%20said%20there's%20a%20basic%20framework%20you%20have%20to%20follow%3A%20%26quot%3BThere's%20me%2C%20there's%20you%2C%20and%20there's%20us.%26quot%3B%20What%20might%20make%20one%20person%20happier%2C%20like%20having%20more%20romantic%20partners%2C%20might%20make%20the%20other%20feel%20neglected.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20a%20non-monogamous%20relationship%20to%20work%2C%20%26quot%3Byou%20want%20to%20be%20able%20to%20both%20navigate%20your%20feelings%20of%20jealousy%2C%26quot%3B%20Garcia%20said.%20Furthermore%2C%20he%20added%2C%20it%20helps%20if%20you%20actively%20enjoy%20knowing%20that%20your%20partner%20is%20with%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20last%20reason%20you%20should%20be%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fis-polyamory-for-you-signs-ready-poly-relationship-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epolyamorous%20or%20open%20relationship%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20because%20you%20want%20it%20to%20%26quot%3Bfix%26quot%3B%20your%20current%20relationship.%20Often%2C%20he%20wrote%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20same%20issues%20that%20plague%20monogamous%20relationships%20%E2%80%94%20mismatched%20libidos%2C%20jealousy%2C%20boredom%2C%20and%20more%20%E2%80%94%20tend%20to%20surface%20in%20consensually%20non-monogamous%20ones.%26quot%3B%20In%20fact%2C%20he%20added%2C%20they%20can%20multiply%20when%20partners%20aren't%20communicating%20or%20devoting%20enough%20time%20to%20each%20other.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20one%20of%20my%20friends%20who%20had%20attempted%20to%20form%20a%20polycule%20once%20told%20me%2C%20'It%20didn't%20work%2C'%26quot%3B%20Garcia%20wrote.%20%26quot%3B'I%20just%20pissed%20off%20two%20women%20instead%20of%20one.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-open-relationship-dont-work-most-people-sex-researcher-2026-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1771676641000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69949816a645d11881897254%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-open-relationship-dont-work-most-people-sex-researcher-2026-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Dr.%20Justin%20R.%20Garcia%2C%20who%20runs%20the%20Kinsey%20Institute%2C%20found%20that%20consensual%20non-monogamy%20doesn't%20work%20for%20most%20people.%20Here's%20why.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jpugachevsky%40businessinsider.com%20(Julia%20Pugachevsky)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A33%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-open-relationship-dont-work-most-people-sex-researcher-2026-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Hedge%20fund%20filings%20reveal%20which%20managers%20started%202026%20exposed%20to%20software%20stocks%20%E2%80%94%20and%20which%20one%20made%20a%20prescient%20bet%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225184%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Greg%20Coffey's%20profile%20taken%20from%20the%20right%20side%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6998932f2237a6a8f0cd8a97%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223456%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EGreg%20Coffey%20held%20a%20large%20bet%20against%20Oracle%20going%20into%202026.%3Cp%3EIan%20MacNicol%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ESeveral%20smaller%20hedge%20funds%20were%20concentrated%20in%20software%20stocks%20at%20the%20start%20of%20the%20year.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ERegulatory%20filings%20show%20former%20Viking%20PM%20Brennan%20Diaz's%20Fernbridge%20was%20a%20big%20holder%20of%20Salesforce.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EOn%20the%20flip%20side%2C%20Greg%20Coffey's%20Kirkoswald%20held%20a%20large%20bet%20against%20Oracle%20to%20start%20the%20year.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20software%20sell-off%20hasn't%20been%20pretty.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThanks%20to%20fears%20that%20artificial%20intelligence%20would%20make%20software%20businesses%20obsolete%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fbusinessinsider.com%2Fai-disruption-stock-selloff-software-tech-real-estate-trucking-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Estocks%20like%20Salesforce%2C%20Oracle%2C%20Workday%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20more%20have%20shed%20trillions%20of%20dollars%20in%20market%20cap.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWho%20in%20the%20%245.2%20trillion%20hedge%20fund%20industry%20has%20been%20stung%20by%20this%20sell-off%20isn't%20entirely%20clear.%20Still%2C%20a%20recent%20release%20of%20regulatory%20filings%20of%20funds'%20holdings%20reveals%20which%20managers%20were%20most%20exposed%20to%20the%20sector%20at%20the%20start%20of%20the%20year.%20It's%20unclear%20if%20these%20funds%20sold%20their%20stakes%20before%20the%20sell-off%20began%20or%20have%20weathered%20the%20losses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20manager%20who%20stands%20out%20is%20Brennan%20Diaz's%20Fernbridge%20Capital%2C%20a%20stockpicking%20fund%20with%20roughly%20%242%20billion%20in%20assets.%20The%20firm%20began%20the%20year%20with%20more%20than%2022%25%20of%20its%20portfolio%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsalesforce-survey-employees-ai-impact-tasks-output-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ein%20Salesforce%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20its%20largest%20position.%20Its%20second-largest%20bet%2C%20which%20made%20up%20nearly%2015%25%20of%20its%20portfolio%20at%20the%20start%20of%202026%2C%20was%20in%20Workday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20two%20stocks%20are%20down%20more%20than%2025%25%20to%20start%20the%20year%2C%20as%20of%20publication%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDiaz%2C%20a%20former%20portfolio%20manager%20at%20Viking%20Global%2C%20started%20the%20fund%20in%202019%2C%20according%20to%20his%20LinkedIn%20profile%2C%20after%20a%20stint%20at%20Junto%20Capital%2C%20another%20fund%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-viking-global-is-top-hedge-fund-launch-training-ground-2021-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Estarted%20by%20a%20Viking%20alum.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EContour%20Asset%20Management%2C%20run%20by%20David%20Meyer%2C%20a%20former%20portfolio%20manager%20at%20European%20multistrategy%20fund%20Brummer%20%26amp%3B%20Partners%2C%20started%20new%20positions%20in%20Salesforce%20and%20Workday%20in%20the%20fourth%20quarter%20of%202025%2C%20filings%20show.%20The%20manager's%20Salesforce%20bet%20was%20its%20third-largest%20holding%20at%202026's%20onset.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20long-running%20activist%20fund%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsalesforce-drafts-plans-to-increase-profits-leaked-document-shows-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EValueAct%20has%20Salesforce%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20its%20largest%20position%2C%20accounting%20for%20more%20than%2011%25%20of%20its%20portfolio%2C%20and%20added%20to%20its%20stake%20in%20the%20fourth%20quarter.%20The%20manager%20has%20been%20invested%20in%20the%20stock%20for%20years%2C%20and%20its%20chief%20investment%20officer%2C%20Mason%20Morfit%2C%20is%20on%20Salesforce's%20board%20of%20directors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESean%20Ma%2C%20who%20ran%20Hong%20Kong-based%20Snow%20Lake%20Capital%20before%20relocating%20to%20California%2C%20started%20M37%20Management%20to%20invest%20in%20AI%20and%20infrastructure.%20His%20firm%20bought%20100%2C000%20shares%20of%20Oracle%20in%20the%20fourth%20quarter%2C%20making%20Larry%20Ellison's%20company%20Ma's%20second-largest%20holding%20at%20the%20start%20of%202026.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20managers%20above%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20least%20one%20fund%20was%20skeptical%20enough%20about%20Oracle%20coming%20into%20the%20year%20that%20it%20was%20willing%20to%20bet%20heavily%20against%20the%20tech%20giant.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKirkoswald's%20Glen%20Coffey%2C%20known%20as%20the%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsohn-coffey-elliott-einhorn-return-to-fundamentals-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EWizard%20of%20Oz%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20for%20his%20macro%20prowess%2C%20bought%20put%20options%20on%20Oracle%20worth%20close%20to%20%24400%20million%20in%20the%20fourth%20quarter%2C%20filings%20show.%20Put%20options%20are%20contracts%20that%20allow%20an%20investor%20to%20sell%20shares%20of%20a%20company%20at%20a%20set%20price%20for%20a%20limited%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EManagers%20use%20them%20to%20bet%20against%20stocks%20they%20expect%20to%20decline%20in%20price%20over%20the%20life%20of%20the%20contract%2C%20because%20the%20structure%20allows%20them%20to%20sell%20a%20stock%20for%20more%20than%20it%20is%20worth%2C%20generating%20a%20profit%20from%20the%20difference.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20unclear%20from%20the%20filings%20how%20long%20Kirkoswald's%20options%20contracts%20were%20for%20or%20whether%20the%20firm%20has%20closed%20any%20positions.%20The%20firm%20declined%20to%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhedge-funds-software-sell-off-2026-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1771676341000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F699893382237a6a8f0cd8a99%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhedge-funds-software-sell-off-2026-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Greg%20Coffey's%20Kirkoswald%20made%20a%20large%20bet%20against%20Oracle%20going%20into%2