th%3D%5C%227462%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22FEBRUARY%2020%3A%20U.S.%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20speaks%20during%20a%20press%20briefing%20at%20the%20White%20House%20on%20February%2020%2C%202026%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC.%20The%20U.S.%20Supreme%20Court%20on%20February%2020%20ruled%20against%20Trump's%20use%20of%20emergency%20powers%20to%20implement%20international%20trade%20tariffs%2C%20a%20central%20portion%20of%20the%20administration's%20core%20economic%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6998fc7e2237a6a8f0cd97e5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225504%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20ruled%20that%20President%20Donald%20Trump's%20IEEPA%20tariffs%20were%20illegal.%3Cp%3EChen%20Mengtong%2FChina%20News%20Service%2FVCG%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20rules%20that%20Trump's%20IEEPA%20tariffs%20are%20illegal.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBusinesses%20are%20celebrating%20the%20SCOTUS%20ruling%2C%20but%20tariff%20refunds%20may%20pose%20a%20fresh%20challenge.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20federal%20government%20could%20be%20on%20the%20hook%20to%20refund%20%24129%20billion.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Trump%20administration's%20cornerstone%20policy%20just%20suffered%20a%20major%20setback%20%E2%80%94%20but%20it's%20not%20bad%20news%20for%20everyone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%206-3%20decision%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsupreme-court-scotus-rules-trump-tariffs-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ESupreme%20Court%20ruled%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Friday%20morning%20that%20the%20president%20does%20not%20have%20the%20authority%20to%20impose%20tariffs%20using%20the%20International%20Emergency%20Economic%20Powers%20Act.%20Most%20of%20the%20tariffs%20Trump%20imposed%20in%202025%2C%20including%20the%20%26quot%3Breciprocal%26quot%3B%20tariffs%20and%20the%2010%25%20baseline%20duties%2C%20made%20under%20IEEPA%2C%20have%20now%20been%20ruled%20illegal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20consumers%20to%20the%20Trump%20administration%2C%20here%20is%20who%20will%20stand%20to%20benefit%20from%20the%20SCOTUS%20ruling%2C%20and%20who%20loses%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22dd08f97b-7270-4d8e-a26f-3aa4d1a6fae0%5C%22%3EThe%20winners%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c7b13cbd-b7bd-4660-9190-b9e524e1f8cc%5C%22%3ETrade%20lawyers%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EBusinesses%2C%20large%20and%20small%2C%20that%20want%20to%20get%20tariff%20money%20back%20from%20the%20US%20government%20will%20need%20lawyers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20made%20it%20clear%20on%20Friday%20that%20the%20US%20government%20will%20not%20make%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-tariff-refund-process-how-works-court-international-trade-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eimmediate%20refunds%3C%2Fa%3E%20despite%20the%20ruling%20that%20the%20IEEPA%20tariffs%20are%20illegal.%20That%20is%20because%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20did%20not%20explicitly%20state%20that%20the%20administration%20needs%20to%20make%20refunds.%20The%20matter%20could%20%26quot%3Bend%20up%20in%20court%20for%20the%20next%20five%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20Trump%20said%20in%20his%20fiery%20remarks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJoyce%20Adetutu%2C%20an%20international%20trade%20lawyer%20at%20Vinson%20%26amp%3B%20Elkins%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20a%20refund%20of%20this%20magnitude%20is%20%26quot%3Bunprecedented%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20the%20process%20will%20likely%20be%20%26quot%3Bdaunting.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPreparing%20for%20refunds%2C%20potential%20litigation%2C%20and%20contract%20interpretations%20will%20likely%20be%20a%20heavy%20lift%20going%20forward%2C%26quot%3B%20Adetutu%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdetutu%20added%20that%20importers%20should%20immediately%20gather%20documentation%2C%20be%20ready%20to%20file%20protests%2C%20and%20plan%20for%20litigation%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERyan%20Petersen%2C%20CEO%20of%20Flexport%2C%20a%20global%20logistics%20company%2C%20wrote%20on%20X%20on%20Friday%20that%20international%20trade%20attorneys%20he%20spoke%20with%20could%20charge%20clients%2015%25%20of%20the%20tariff%20refund%20amount%20to%20help%20them%20claim%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226eb51155-0662-4868-83fd-9cb7429e7e3a%5C%22%3ETrump's%20political%20foes%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EDemocratic%20lawmakers%20are%20now%20calling%20for%20Trump%20to%20hand%20out%20tariff%20refund%20checks%20to%20households.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDonald%20Trump%20should%20return%20that%20money%20immediately.%20He%20has%20an%20obligation%2C%26quot%3B%20California%20Gov.%20Gavin%20Newsom%20said%20on%20Friday.%20%26quot%3BHe%20took%20hundreds%20of%20billions%20of%20dollars%20from%20working%20folks%2C%20from%20the%20ag%20community%2C%20from%20small%20businesses%20for%20this%20vanity%20play%2C%20this%20illegal%20action%2C%20and%20he%20finally%20was%20held%20to%20account.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIllinois%20Gov.%20JB%20Pritzker%20sent%20Trump%20an%20%26quot%3Binvoice%26quot%3B%20letter%20to%20Trump.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOn%20behalf%20of%20the%20people%20of%20Illinois%2C%20I%20demand%20a%20refund%20of%20%241%2C700%20for%20every%20family%20in%20Illinois%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22daa150fb-0b21-4543-a801-624f2501c369%5C%22%3ELosers%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229e373e74-ad98-4b09-82d1-121d72328b23%5C%22%3EThe%20US%20government%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20only%20did%20the%20decision%20upend%20a%20cornerstone%20of%20Trump's%20economic%20agenda%2C%20but%20the%20federal%20government%20could%20be%20on%20the%20hook%20for%20a%20huge%20sum%20of%20money%20as%20US%20companies%20and%20importers%20fight%20to%20claw%20back%20the%20tariffs%20they%20paid.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20Customs%20and%20Border%20Protection%2C%20as%20of%20December%2010%2C%202025%2C%20a%20total%20of%20over%2034%20million%20entries%20subject%20to%20IEEPA%20duties%20have%20been%20made%20by%20over%20301%2C000%20importers%2C%20amounting%20to%20around%20%24129%20billion%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-tariffs-paid-almost-entirely-by-americans-german-study-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etariff%20revenue%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Committee%20for%20a%20Responsible%20Budget%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20to%20Business%20Insider%20that%20the%20tariff%20ruling%20will%20reduce%20revenues%20on%20net%20by%20%241.9%20trillion%20through%20Fiscal%20Year%202036%20and%20increase%20debt%20by%20%242.4%20trillion%20over%20the%20same%20period%2C%20assuming%20the%20tariffs%20are%20refunded%20without%20replacement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPresident%20Trump%20has%20been%20abundantly%20clear%3A%20Tariffs%20are%20here%20to%20stay%2C%20and%20the%20America%20Last%20era%20of%20American%20workers%20being%20ripped%20off%20is%20over%2C%26quot%3B%20White%20House%20Spokesman%20Kush%20Desai%20previously%20told%20Business%20Insider%20in%20a%20statement%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20administration%20would%20find%20other%20avenues%20for%20Trump's%20trade%20and%20economic%20agenda.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEither%20way%2C%20tariffs%20and%20the%20impact%20of%20the%20ruling%20could%20complicate%20a%202026%20midterm%20election%20message%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20on%20affordability.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d54cc189-df03-49d0-b466-c52bd773a0bd%5C%22%3EIt's%20complicated%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22012c1ad9-958f-4971-9b8e-cab863c7d096%5C%22%3EConsumers%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EAmerican%20households%20could%20see%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprices-food-coffee-gas-clothes-pets-rent-survey-inflation-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einflation%20and%20prices%3C%2Fa%3E%20ease%2C%20but%20it%20may%20not%20happen%20quickly%20%E2%80%94%20and%20it%20may%20not%20happen%20across%20all%20goods%2C%20depending%20on%20additional%20tariffs%20implemented.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20New%20York%20Fed's%20Research%20and%20Statistics%20Group%2C%20along%20with%20research%20analyst%20Chris%20Flanagan%20and%20economist%20Sebastian%20Heise%2C%20found%20that%2094%25%20of%20tariffs%20were%20paid%20by%20domestic%20businesses%20and%20consumers%20in%20the%20first%20eight%20months%20of%202025.%20The%20Federal%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20St.%20Louis%20separately%20wrote%20in%20October%202025%20that%20tariffs%20are%20exerting%20%26quot%3Bmeasurable%20upward%20pressure%26quot%3B%20on%20consumer%20prices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJosh%20Ketter%2C%20CEO%20of%20Spreetail%2C%20a%20top%20100%20US%20importer%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20there%20may%20not%20be%20immediate%20price%20cuts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRetailers%20haven't%20passed%20on%20the%20full%20cost%20of%20tariffs%20to%20consumers%20over%20the%20past%20year%3B%20instead%2C%20they've%20seen%20their%20margins%20squeezed%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Ketter.%20%26quot%3BTheir%20first%20priority%20for%20tariff%20refunds%20will%20be%20to%20make%20themselves%20financially%20whole%20again.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%2C%20of%20course%2C%20the%20tariffs%20are%20not%20completely%20going%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%2C%20issued%20under%20other%20statutes%2C%20remain%2C%20and%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20on%20Friday%20signed%20a%20proclamation%20imposing%2010%25%20tariffs%20for%20150%20days%2C%20starting%20on%20February%2024%2C%20under%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-tariff-law-options-supreme-court-decision-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESection%20122%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20Trade%20Act%20of%201974.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20exemptions%20for%20certain%20categories%2C%20according%20to%20the%20proclamation%2C%20including%20critical%20minerals%20and%20some%20agricultural%20products%2C%20and%20prices%20could%20come%20down%20for%20exempt%20items.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b70e23ca-5435-4c55-8dd4-150bec081255%5C%22%3EBusinesses%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3ESmall%20businesses%20that%20led%20the%20charge%20against%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsupreme-court-scotus-rules-trump-tariffs-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EIEEPA%20tariffs%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20celebrating.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20impossible%20to%20describe%20the%20feeling%20of%20elation%2C%20of%20seeing%20that%20yes%2C%20we%20were%20right%20and%20the%20court%20agrees%20with%20us%2C%20and%20a%20feeling%20that%20justice%20prevailed%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flead-plaintiff-in-case-against-trumps-tariffs-wine-improting-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EVictor%20Schwartz%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20lead%20plaintiff%20in%20the%20case%20against%20tariffs%20and%20the%20owner%20of%20VOS%20Selections%2C%20in%20a%20media%20event%20on%20Friday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVOS%20Selections%20is%20a%20wine-importing%20company%20based%20in%20New%20York%20that%20specializes%20in%20European%20specialty%20wines.%20For%20now%2C%20the%20company%20will%20have%20more%20cash%20flow%20from%20no%20longer%20needing%20to%20pay%20tariffs%20upfront%20before%20a%20single%20bottle%20of%20wine%20even%20sells.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESchwartz%20said%20the%20amount%20of%20tariffs%20his%20company%20has%20paid%20so%20far%20sits%20in%20the%20%26quot%3Blow%20six%20figures%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20he%20doesn't%20know%20when%20he%20could%20see%20a%20refund.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPer%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EHong%2C%20global%20lead%20of%20Kearney%20Foresight%2C%20however%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20companies%20should%20not%20assume%20rapid%20balance-sheet%20relief.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAny%20reimbursement%20process%20is%20likely%20to%20move%20through%20the%20customs%20liquidation%20system%20and%20would%20be%20administratively%20slow%2C%20burdensome%2C%20and%20likely%20drawn%20out%20over%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Hong.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELarge%20global%20companies%2C%20including%20Costco%2C%20Toyota%2C%20and%20Chinese%20EV%20maker%20BYD%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.